cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT

The paper discusses hierarchical architectures for learning from examples, which is a common topic in machine learning. The focus on Deep Convolutional Neural Networks suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of activation functions and the discussion of function approximation also suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The mention of convolutional neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The discussion of learning from examples and function approximation is also relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mention of complexity reduction suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
